57const char *program = "dnssec-importkey";
58int verbose;
59
60static dns_rdataclass_t rdclass;
61static dns_fixedname_t fixed;
62static dns_name_t *name = NULL;
63static isc_mem_t *mctx = NULL;
64static bool setpub = false, setdel = false;
65static bool setttl = false;
66static isc_stdtime_t pub = 0, del = 0;
67static dns_ttl_t ttl = 0;
68static isc_stdtime_t syncadd = 0, syncdel = 0;
69static bool setsyncadd = false;
70static bool setsyncdel = false;
71
72static isc_result_t
73initname(char *setname) {
74 isc_result_t result;
75 isc_buffer_t buf;
76
77 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
78
79 isc_buffer_init(&buf, setname, strlen(setname));
80 isc_buffer_add(&buf, strlen(setname));
81 result = dns_name_fromtext(name, &buf, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
82 return (result);
83}
84
85static void
86db_load_from_stream(dns_db_t *db, FILE *fp) {
87 isc_result_t result;
88 dns_rdatacallbacks_t callbacks;
89
90 dns_rdatacallbacks_init(&callbacks);
91 result = dns_db_beginload(db, &callbacks);
92 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
93 fatal("dns_db_beginload failed: %s", isc_result_totext(result));
94
95 result = dns_master_loadstream(fp, name, name, rdclass, 0,
96 &callbacks, mctx);
97 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
98 fatal("can't load from input: %s", isc_result_totext(result));
99
100 result = dns_db_endload(db, &callbacks);
101 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
102 fatal("dns_db_endload failed: %s", isc_result_totext(result));
103}
104
105static isc_result_t
106loadset(const char *filename, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
107 isc_result_t result;
108 dns_db_t *db = NULL;
109 dns_dbnode_t *node = NULL;
110 char setname[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
111
112 dns_name_format(name, setname, sizeof(setname));
113
114 result = dns_db_create(mctx, "rbt", name, dns_dbtype_zone,
115 rdclass, 0, NULL, &db);
116 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
117 fatal("can't create database");
118
119 if (strcmp(filename, "-") == 0) {
120 db_load_from_stream(db, stdin);
121 filename = "input";
122 } else {
123 result = dns_db_load(db, filename, dns_masterformat_text,
124 DNS_MASTER_NOTTL);
125 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_SEENINCLUDE)
126 fatal("can't load %s: %s", filename,
127 isc_result_totext(result));
128 }
129
130 result = dns_db_findnode(db, name, false, &node);
131 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
132 fatal("can't find %s node in %s", setname, filename);
133
134 result = dns_db_findrdataset(db, node, NULL, dns_rdatatype_dnskey,
135 0, 0, rdataset, NULL);
136
137 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
138 fatal("no DNSKEY RR for %s in %s", setname, filename);
139 else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
140 fatal("dns_db_findrdataset");
141
142 if (node != NULL)
143 dns_db_detachnode(db, &node);
144 if (db != NULL)
145 dns_db_detach(&db);
146 return (result);
147}
148
149static void
150loadkey(char *filename, unsigned char *key_buf, unsigned int key_buf_size,
151 dns_rdata_t *rdata)
152{
153 isc_result_t result;
154 dst_key_t *key = NULL;
155 isc_buffer_t keyb;
156 isc_region_t r;
157
158 dns_rdata_init(rdata);
159
160 isc_buffer_init(&keyb, key_buf, key_buf_size);
161
162 result = dst_key_fromnamedfile(filename, NULL, DST_TYPE_PUBLIC,
163 mctx, &key);
164 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
165 fatal("invalid keyfile name %s: %s",
166 filename, isc_result_totext(result));
167
168 if (verbose > 2) {
169 char keystr[DST_KEY_FORMATSIZE];
170
171 dst_key_format(key, keystr, sizeof(keystr));
172 fprintf(stderr, "%s: %s\n", program, keystr);
173 }
174
175 result = dst_key_todns(key, &keyb);
176 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
177 fatal("can't decode key");
178
179 isc_buffer_usedregion(&keyb, &r);
180 dns_rdata_fromregion(rdata, dst_key_class(key),
181 dns_rdatatype_dnskey, &r);
182
183 rdclass = dst_key_class(key);
184
185 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
186 result = dns_name_copy(dst_key_name(key), name, NULL);
187 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
188 fatal("can't copy name");
189
190 dst_key_free(&key);
191}
192
193static void
194emit(const char *dir, dns_rdata_t *rdata) {
195 isc_result_t result;
196 char keystr[DST_KEY_FORMATSIZE];
197 char pubname[1024];
198 char priname[1024];
199 isc_buffer_t buf;
200 dst_key_t *key = NULL, *tmp = NULL;
201
202 isc_buffer_init(&buf, rdata->data, rdata->length);
203 isc_buffer_add(&buf, rdata->length);
204 result = dst_key_fromdns(name, rdclass, &buf, mctx, &key);
205 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
206 fatal("dst_key_fromdns: %s", isc_result_totext(result));
207 }
208
209 isc_buffer_init(&buf, pubname, sizeof(pubname));
210 result = dst_key_buildfilename(key, DST_TYPE_PUBLIC, dir, &buf);
211 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
212 fatal("Failed to build public key filename: %s",
213 isc_result_totext(result));
214 }
215 isc_buffer_init(&buf, priname, sizeof(priname));
216 result = dst_key_buildfilename(key, DST_TYPE_PRIVATE, dir, &buf);
217 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
218 fatal("Failed to build private key filename: %s",
219 isc_result_totext(result));
220 }
221
222 result = dst_key_fromfile(dst_key_name(key), dst_key_id(key),
223 dst_key_alg(key),
224 DST_TYPE_PUBLIC | DST_TYPE_PRIVATE,
225 dir, mctx, &tmp);
226 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
227 if (dst_key_isprivate(tmp) && !dst_key_isexternal(tmp))
228 fatal("Private key already exists in %s", priname);
229 dst_key_free(&tmp);
230 }
231
232 dst_key_setexternal(key, true);
233 if (setpub)
234 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_PUBLISH, pub);
235 if (setdel)
236 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_DELETE, del);
237 if (setsyncadd)
238 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCPUBLISH, syncadd);
239 if (setsyncdel)
240 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCDELETE, syncdel);
241
242 if (setttl)
243 dst_key_setttl(key, ttl);
244
245 result = dst_key_tofile(key, DST_TYPE_PUBLIC|DST_TYPE_PRIVATE,
246 dir);
247 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
248 dst_key_format(key, keystr, sizeof(keystr));
249 fatal("Failed to write key %s: %s", keystr,
250 isc_result_totext(result));
251 }
252 printf("%s\n", pubname);
253
254 isc_buffer_clear(&buf);
255 result = dst_key_buildfilename(key, DST_TYPE_PRIVATE, dir, &buf);
256 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
257 fatal("Failed to build private key filename: %s",
258 isc_result_totext(result));
259 }
260 printf("%s\n", priname);
261 dst_key_free(&key);
262}
263
264ISC_PLATFORM_NORETURN_PRE static void
265usage(void) ISC_PLATFORM_NORETURN_POST;
266
267static void
268usage(void) {
269 fprintf(stderr, "Usage:\n");
270 fprintf(stderr, " %s options [-K dir] keyfile\n\n", program);
271 fprintf(stderr, " %s options -f file [keyname]\n\n", program);
272 fprintf(stderr, "Version: %s\n", VERSION);
273 fprintf(stderr, "Options:\n");
274 fprintf(stderr, " -f file: read key from zone file\n");
275 fprintf(stderr, " -K <directory>: directory in which to store "
276 "the key files\n");
277 fprintf(stderr, " -L ttl: set default key TTL\n");
278 fprintf(stderr, " -v <verbose level>\n");
279 fprintf(stderr, " -V: print version information\n");
280 fprintf(stderr, " -h: print usage and exit\n");
281 fprintf(stderr, "Timing options:\n");
282 fprintf(stderr, " -P date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
283 "publication date\n");
284 fprintf(stderr, " -P sync date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset "
285 "CDS and CDNSKEY publication date\n");
286 fprintf(stderr, " -D date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
287 "deletion date\n");
288 fprintf(stderr, " -D sync date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset "
289 "CDS and CDNSKEY deletion date\n");
290
291 exit (-1);
292}
293
294int
295main(int argc, char **argv) {
296 char *classname = NULL;
297 char *filename = NULL, *dir = NULL, *namestr;
298 char *endp;
299 int ch;
300 isc_result_t result;
301 isc_log_t *log = NULL;
302 dns_rdataset_t rdataset;
303 dns_rdata_t rdata;
304 isc_stdtime_t now;
305
306 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
307 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
308
309 if (argc == 1)
310 usage();
311
312 result = isc_mem_create(0, 0, &mctx);
313 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
314 fatal("out of memory");
315
316#if USE_PKCS11
317 pk11_result_register();
318#endif
319 dns_result_register();
320
321 isc_commandline_errprint = false;
322
323#define CMDLINE_FLAGS "D:f:hK:L:P:v:V"
324 while ((ch = isc_commandline_parse(argc, argv, CMDLINE_FLAGS)) != -1) {
325 switch (ch) {
326 case 'D':
327 /* -Dsync ? */
328 if (isoptarg("sync", argv, usage)) {
329 if (setsyncdel)
330 fatal("-D sync specified more than "
331 "once");
332
333 syncdel = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
334 now, now, &setsyncdel);
335 break;
336 }
337 /* -Ddnskey ? */
338 (void)isoptarg("dnskey", argv, usage);
339 if (setdel)
340 fatal("-D specified more than once");
341
342 del = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
343 now, now, &setdel);
344 break;
345 case 'K':
346 dir = isc_commandline_argument;
347 if (strlen(dir) == 0U)
348 fatal("directory must be non-empty string");
349 break;
350 case 'L':
351 ttl = strtottl(isc_commandline_argument);
352 setttl = true;
353 break;
354 case 'P':
355 /* -Psync ? */
356 if (isoptarg("sync", argv, usage)) {
357 if (setsyncadd)
358 fatal("-P sync specified more than "
359 "once");
360
361 syncadd = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
362 now, now, &setsyncadd);
363 break;
364 }
365 /* -Pdnskey ? */
366 (void)isoptarg("dnskey", argv, usage);
367 if (setpub)
368 fatal("-P specified more than once");
369
370 pub = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
371 now, now, &setpub);
372 break;
373 case 'f':
374 filename = isc_commandline_argument;
375 break;
376 case 'v':
377 verbose = strtol(isc_commandline_argument, &endp, 0);
378 if (*endp != '\0')
379 fatal("-v must be followed by a number");
380 break;
381 case '?':
382 if (isc_commandline_option != '?')
383 fprintf(stderr, "%s: invalid argument -%c\n",
384 program, isc_commandline_option);
385 /* FALLTHROUGH */
386 case 'h':
387 /* Does not return. */
388 usage();
389
390 case 'V':
391 /* Does not return. */
392 version(program);
393
394 default:
395 fprintf(stderr, "%s: unhandled option -%c\n",
396 program, isc_commandline_option);
397 exit(1);
398 }
399 }
400
401 rdclass = strtoclass(classname);
402
403 if (argc < isc_commandline_index + 1 && filename == NULL)
404 fatal("the key file name was not specified");
405 if (argc > isc_commandline_index + 1)
406 fatal("extraneous arguments");
407
408 result = dst_lib_init(mctx, NULL);
409 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
410 fatal("could not initialize dst: %s",
411 isc_result_totext(result));
412
413 setup_logging(mctx, &log);
414
415 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset);
416
417 if (filename != NULL) {
418 if (argc < isc_commandline_index + 1) {
419 /* using filename as zone name */
420 namestr = filename;
421 } else
422 namestr = argv[isc_commandline_index];
423
424 result = initname(namestr);
425 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
426 fatal("could not initialize name %s", namestr);
427
428 result = loadset(filename, &rdataset);
429
430 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
431 fatal("could not load DNSKEY set: %s\n",
432 isc_result_totext(result));
433
434 for (result = dns_rdataset_first(&rdataset);
435 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS;
436 result = dns_rdataset_next(&rdataset)) {
437
438 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
439 dns_rdataset_current(&rdataset, &rdata);
440 emit(dir, &rdata);
441 }
442 } else {
443 unsigned char key_buf[DST_KEY_MAXSIZE];
444
445 loadkey(argv[isc_commandline_index], key_buf,
446 DST_KEY_MAXSIZE, &rdata);
447
448 emit(dir, &rdata);
449 }
450
451 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&rdataset))
452 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset);
453 cleanup_logging(&log);
454 dst_lib_destroy();
455 dns_name_destroy();
456 if (verbose > 10)
457 isc_mem_stats(mctx, stdout);
458 isc_mem_destroy(&mctx);
459
460 fflush(stdout);
461 if (ferror(stdout)) {
462 fprintf(stderr, "write error\n");
463 return (1);
464 } else
465 return (0);
466}
